.TH git-uptodate 1 "November 2025" "git-uptodate"
.SH NAME
git-uptodate \- print branch, stash, and working tree status for one or more repositories
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-uptodate
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ directory ... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git-uptodate
prints local repository status including tracked and untracked changes,
stashes, and branch divergence for for one or more repositories. Remotes
are always refreshed via
.B git remote update --prune
so ahead/behind counts are accurate. When no directories are supplied the
current working directory is scanned.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show usage information and exit.
.TP
.B --pull
Attempt to fast-forward merge the current branch after updating remotes.
.TP
.I directory
One or more directories to scan recursively for Git repositories. If none
are given the current directory is used.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns zero on success, non-zero if an error occurs.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B git-uptodate
Scan the current directory.
.TP
.B git-uptodate ~/src
Scan all repositories under \fI~/src\fP.
.TP
.B git uptodate -- --pull
Run through the \fBgit\fP front end and fast-forward the active branches.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git (1)
